            "title": "Ipsen provides update on Phase III BOLD trial in biliary atresia",
            "id": "dd718819-0bb3-4416-8fc2-1416db190695",
            "description": "On 24 July 2026, Ipsen shared that the Phase III BOLD trial comparing Bylvay to placebo for patients with biliary atresia (BA) post-Kasai hepatoportoenterostomy (HPE) did not achieve the primary outcome of enhancing native liver survival compared to placebo. The latest data aligns with the known safety profile of odevixibat in authorized uses. BA, a swift-progressing and intricate condition, stands as the primary reason for pediatric liver transplants, lacking approved treatments aside from Kasai HPE or liver transplants. Ipsen is listed on Euronext as IPN and on ADR as IPSEY.",
